.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-PLUGIN-STOP" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-plugin-stop \- unload a running plugin from the daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-plugin-stop
.I plugin_name
.SH DESCRIPTION
Calls
.B lightning-cli plugin stop
to unload the named plugin at runtime.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable or the plugin is not found.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-plugin-list (1),
.BR lightning-node-plugin-start (1)
